                <!-- Information Section -->
                <div class="col-md-6 fade-in-right">
                    <h2 class="section-heading text-uppercase">Our Technology</h2>
                    <p class="section-subheading text-muted">
                        Foam clothing, invented by survival expert Jim Phillips, uses <strong>open-cell polyurethane foam</strong> to provide life-saving insulation even in freezing temperatures. This innovative material retains body heat effectively, even when wet, as long as synthetic fabrics are worn instead of cotton. By combining <strong>breathable, moisture-wicking synthetic layers</strong>, our vests offer durability and comfort while reducing moisture as a life-threatening factor in the cold.
                    </p>
                    <p class="section-subheading text-muted">
                        Typically sold at high costs in emergency preparedness markets, we’ve made this <strong>life-saving technology affordable and accessible</strong>. Turtle Shelter Vests harness body heat to keep users warm in extreme conditions, offering <strong>durable foam insulation and functional designs</strong> like adjustable hoods, belts, and pockets. Our mission is to alleviate suffering and save lives for those living in their emergency every single day.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
